The Crookshank Assignment Cases. (Sarah Benedict v. John C. Crookshank and David C. Crookshank.) Costs on affirmance by equal division. June 11. Sept. 29. Mitchel c& McGarry for defendants appellant L. II. Jennings and Morse, Wilson <& TrovSbridge for claimant appellee.

Costs were withheld where, on review, the court was equally divided.

Error to Ionia. (Montgomery, J.)
